Use this class to create a general object-tree using the Gson parser (see http://code.google.com/p/google-gson/). This class deserializes Gson output such that all objects are one of the following types:

  • String
  • Boolean
  • Number (may be Integer, Double, BigInteger, or BigDecimal per gson)
  • Object[] (where each element is also one of these 5 types)
  • Map (where each value is one of these 5 types)
This is often useful when creating a complete new specific deserializer is too much work because just a specific subset of the output is desired, or for when it isn't known exactly in advance which object maps to any given json input.
